* synchronize to backing db
   - keep a server_version field in local db
   - keep a version field in local, remote
   - add an "exists on remote" field, renumber cids when uploading to
       remote. Alert to conflicts by nom/prenom/ddn with already-existing 
       members.
       * actually the server_version = -1 field does that.
   - when updating: 
      /* invariant: local version >= local server_version */
      if local server_version = remote ver, we can freely update:
        if local version = local server_version, no changes
        if local version > local server_version, push to server

      if local server_version < remote ver, 
        if local version = local server_version, pull from server
        if local version > local server_version, merge changes

      if local server_version > remote ver: should not happen.

